                            <comment id="13395540" author="mvalverde" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2007 07:06:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sorry, did not find a way to reopen the original issue, but this isn&apos;t solved! &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13395542" author="dotteben" created="Mon, 2 Apr 2007 10:41:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hit this one as well. It is a particular problem when you need the expression to short-circuit to avoid getting a stack trace from the 2nd expression getting evaluated. For example:&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;showCrumbs jwcid=&quot;@If&quot; condition=&quot;ognl:categoryId != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; ancestors.size &amp;gt; 1&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;getAncestors() depends on the fact that getCategoryId() is not null. This one worked in OGNL 2.6, it throws an exception in 2.7.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
